                     <div class="columns large-12 medium-12 small-12 mainContentFullWidth">
                        <div class="content">
                           <h1>Academics &amp; Training</h1>
                           
                           <p><span class="intro-paragraph">Mt. San Antonio College is proud to offer more than 260 different academic and training
                                 programs for our students. No matter what career you want to pursue, four-year university
                                 you want to transfer to, or skill you want to learn, Mt. SAC has a program for you.
                                 Browse the links below to explore the programs that are right for you.</span></p>
                           
                           <div class="row">
                              <div class="small-12 large-12 columns">
                                 <div class="circleicons-wrapper">
                                    <ul class="large-block-grid-6 medium-block-grid-3 small-block-grid-2">
                                       <li><a href="/catalog/index.html" title="" target=""><span class="ci circleiconsimgs" style="background-color:transparent"><img class="cicon" src="/academics-and-training/images/catalog_icon.png" alt="College Catalog" width="120" height="120"></span><br><span class="linktext">College Catalog</span></a></li>
                                       <li><a href="/schedule/calendar.html" title="" target=""><span class="ci circleiconsimgs" style="background-color:transparent"><img class="cicon" src="/academics-and-training/images/academics_calendar_icon.png" alt="Academic Calendar" width="120" height="120"></span><br><span class="linktext">Academic Calendar</span></a></li>
                                       <li><a href="/continuinged/" title="" target=""><span class="ci circleiconsimgs" style="background-color:transparent"><img class="cicon" src="/academics-and-training/images/continuing_ed_icon.png" alt="Continuing Education" width="120" height="120"></span><br><span class="linktext">Continuing Education</span></a></li>
                                       <li><a href="/instruction/divisions.html" title="" target=""><span class="ci circleiconsimgs" style="background-color:transparent"><img class="cicon" src="/academics-and-training/images/departments_icon.png" alt="Academic Departments" width="120" height="120"></span><br><span class="linktext">Academic Departments</span></a></li>
                                       <li><a href="/schedule/index.html" title="" target=""><span class="ci circleiconsimgs" style="background-color:transparent"><img class="cicon" src="/academics-and-training/images/class_schedule_icon.png" alt="schedule of classes" width="120" height="120"></span><br><span class="linktext">Schedule of Classes</span></a></li>
                                       <li><a href="/admissions/steps-to-apply/index.html" title="" target=""><span class="ci circleiconsimgs" style="background-color:transparent"><img class="cicon" src="/academics-and-training/images/apply_icon.png" alt="Steps to Apply" width="120" height="120"></span><br><span class="linktext">Steps to Apply</span></a></li>
                                    </ul>
                                 </div>
                              </div>
                           </div>
                           
                           <div class="row 3columncontent" data-equalizer="column_height_equal">
                              <div class="small-12 medium-4 large-4 columns content_grid" data-equalizer-watch="column_height_equal" style="float:left;">
                                 <div style="background-image:url(/academics-and-training/images/online.jpg); background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; min-height:300px; background-position: center center; width: 100%; display: block; margin: 0 auto;" title="A student works in class." class="3columncntbgimg"><span class="hide">A student works in class.</span></div>
                                 
                                 <h2><span>Online Programs</span></h2>
                                 
                                 <p><span>Mt. San Antonio College's robust online program provides an affordable and convenient
                                       way for students to reach their academic goals. The college has more than 3,000 online
                                       classes.</span></p>
                                 
                                 <ul>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/online/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mt. SAC Online</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/online/online-classes.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Search for online classes and programs</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/online/student-resources.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Online Student Resources</a></li>
                                    
                                 </ul>
                                 
                              </div>
                              <div class="small-12 medium-4 large-4 columns content_grid" data-equalizer-watch="column_height_equal" style="float:left;">
                                 <div style="background-image:url(/academics-and-training/images/slide2.jpg); background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; min-height:300px; background-position: center center; width: 100%; display: block; margin: 0 auto;" title="Students at graduation" class="3columncntbgimg"><span class="hide">Students at graduation</span></div>
                                 
                                 <h2><span>Associate Degrees</span></h2>
                                 
                                 <p><span>Some of our students choose to earn their associate degrees to prepare for a career,
                                       and others earn a degree to prepare for transfer to a four-year university. &nbsp;With
                                       more than 90 degree programs to choose from, you will find the right degree program
                                       for your goals.&nbsp;</span></p>
                                 
                                 <ul>
                                    
                                    <li><a title="View Degrees &amp; Majors organized alphabetically" href="https://catalog.mtsac.edu/programs/programsaz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Associate Degrees</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a title="Associate Degrees for Transfer to CSU" href="/transfer/transfer_associate_degrees.html">Associate Degrees for Transfer to CSU</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/distancelearning/index.html">Online Learning (Distance Learning)</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/instruction/divisions.html">Office of Instruction - Divisions and Departments</a>&nbsp;
                                    </li>
                                    
                                 </ul>
                                 
                              </div>
                              <div class="small-12 medium-4 large-4 columns content_grid" data-equalizer-watch="column_height_equal" style="float:left;">
                                 <div style="background-image:url(/academics-and-training/images/slide3.JPG); background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; min-height:300px; background-position: center center; width: 100%; display: block; margin: 0 auto;" title="Student tending to plants. " class="3columncntbgimg"><span class="hide">Student tending to plants. </span></div>
                                 
                                 <h2><span>Certificates &amp;&nbsp;Career Education</span></h2>
                                 
                                 <p><span>Certificates can be a great option for students who want career training to advance
                                       in their current job or learn a new trade. Some of our most popular certificate programs
                                       are Engineering Technology, Industrial Design Engineering, Consumer Relations, Business
                                       Management, Welding, Fire Technology, Law Enforcement, and Programming.&nbsp;</span></p>
                                 
                                 <ul>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/ce/">Career Education</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/instruction/certificates.html">Certificates</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/distancelearning/index.html">Online Learning (Distance Learning)</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/instruction/divisions.html">Office of Instruction - Divisions and Departments</a></li>
                                    
                                 </ul>
                                 
                              </div>
                           </div>
                           <div class="clearfix"></div>
                           
                           <div class="row 3columncontent" data-equalizer="column_height_equal">
                              <div class="small-12 medium-4 large-4 columns content_grid" data-equalizer-watch="column_height_equal" style="float:left;">
                                 <div style="background-image:url(/academics-and-training/images/slide4.jpg); background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; min-height:300px; background-position: center center; width: 100%; display: block; margin: 0 auto;" title="Student in a vocational field" class="3columncntbgimg"><span class="hide">Student in a vocational field</span></div>
                                 
                                 <h2><span>Vocational Programs</span></h2>
                                 
                                 <p><span>For students who want to learn a new trade or upgrade their&nbsp;skills, but do not want
                                       or need college credit for their courses, we offer more than 55 noncredit vocational
                                       programs to prepare students for careers. These programs include fee-based and no-cost
                                       courses in health careers,&nbsp;accounting, welding, photography, medical training, manufacturing,
                                       and more. Learn about all of our noncredit vocational programs at the links below.</span></p>
                                 
                                 <ul>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/vocational/">Adult and Continuing Education - Health Programs</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/vocational/">Adult and Continuing Education - Vocational Certificates</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/continuinged/">Adult and Continuing Education Home</a></li>
                                    
                                 </ul>
                                 
                              </div>
                              <div class="small-12 medium-4 large-4 columns content_grid" data-equalizer-watch="column_height_equal" style="float:left;">
                                 <div style="background-image:url(/academics-and-training/images/slide5.jpg); background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; min-height:300px; background-position: center center; width: 100%; display: block; margin: 0 auto;" title="Two women talking outside Building 66." class="3columncntbgimg"><span class="hide">Two women talking outside Building 66.</span></div>
                                 
                                 <h2><span>Adult Education (under Adult and Continuing Education)</span></h2>
                                 
                                 <p><span>Mt. SAC offers quality programs and services to meet the needs of all students.&nbsp;We
                                       have </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">no-cost&nbsp;programs</span><span> to help students of all ages build pathways toward career and college goals. Students
                                       can earn a&nbsp;high school diploma or equivalency, prepare for the military exam, gain
                                       computer skills, learn English, and strengthen self-sufficiency. Services such as
                                       counseling and career development support student success.&nbsp;</span></p>
                                 
                                 <ul>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/abe/">Adult Basic Education</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/highschool/">Adult High School Diploma</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/oap/">Education for Older Adults</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/esl/index.html">ESL (English as a Second Language)</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/abe/ged_prep.html">High School Equivalency (GED/HiSET)</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/highschoolreferral/index.html">High School Referral</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/continuinged/">Adult and Continuing Education Home</a></li>
                                    
                                 </ul>
                                 
                              </div>
                              <div class="small-12 medium-4 large-4 columns content_grid" data-equalizer-watch="column_height_equal" style="float:left;">
                                 <div style="background-image:url(/academics-and-training/images/slide6.jpg); background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; min-height:300px; background-position: center center; width: 100%; display: block; margin: 0 auto;" title="Professor teaching students" class="3columncntbgimg"><span class="hide">Professor teaching students</span></div>
                                 
                                 <h2><span>Community &amp;&nbsp;Personal Enrichment Courses (fee-based)</span></h2>
                                 
                                 <p><span>As a community college, we are here to serve our community through education. Community
                                       members can enroll in fee-based classes in topics that interest them, such as financial
                                       planning, computer literacy, CPR, or home improvement. We also offer activity classes
                                       in motorcycle training, martial arts, swim, tennis, and more for children and adults.&nbsp;</span></p>
                                 
                                 <ul>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="http://communityed.mtsac.edu/">Community Education</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/continuinged/">Adult and Continuing Education Home</a></li>
                                    
                                 </ul>
                                 
                              </div>
                           </div>
                           <div class="clearfix"></div>
                           
                           <div class="row 3columncontent" data-equalizer="column_height_equal">
                              <div class="small-12 medium-4 large-4 columns content_grid" data-equalizer-watch="column_height_equal" style="float:left;">
                                 <div style="background-image:url(/academics-and-training/images/slide1.jpg); background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; min-height:300px; background-position: center center; width: 100%; display: block; margin: 0 auto;" title="A student works in class." class="3columncntbgimg"><span class="hide">A student works in class.</span></div>
                                 
                                 <h2><span>Bachelor Degrees</span></h2>
                                 
                                 <p><span>Students can save almost half the cost of their education by beginning their education
                                       at Mt. SAC and then transferring to a four-year university. In addition, Mt. SAC has
                                       partnered with several universities to provide accelerated bachelor's degrees (often
                                       with reduced tuition). Classes are conveniently held online or at Mt. SAC.</span></p>
                                 
                                 <ul>
                                    
                                    <li><a title="Transferring to 4-Year University" href="/transfer/index.html">Transferring to 4-Year University</a></li>
                                    
                                    <li><a href="/academics-and-training/bachelors-programs.html">Bachelor Degrees on the Mt. SAC Campus</a></li>
                                    
                                 </ul>
                                 
                              </div>
                              <div class="small-12 medium-4 large-4 columns content_grid" data-equalizer-watch="column_height_equal" style="float:left;">
                                 
                                 <p>&nbsp;</p>
                                 
                              </div>
                              <div class="small-12 medium-4 large-4 columns content_grid" data-equalizer-watch="column_height_equal" style="float:left;">
                                 
                                 <p>&nbsp;</p>
                                 
                              </div>
                           </div>
